{"event_id": "evt_20260211_terminal_rendering_fix", "ts": "2026-02-11T16:48:12.977628+00:00", "agent": "CLAUDE", "role": "Frontend_Engineer", "action_type": "bug_fix", "description": "Fixed terminal rendering bug: lines disappearing when text exceeds viewport. Root cause: term.open() was called on a hidden wrapper (display:none), so xterm.js measured 0 font/cell dimensions, causing wrong row count. Fix: (1) wrapper made visible before term.open() by setting active class immediately, (2) removed .xterm position:absolute override that conflicted with xterm.js internal viewport layout, replaced with height:100%, (3) replaced setTimeout timing hacks with requestAnimationFrame, (4) removed forced scrollToBottom on every PTY output chunk.", "spec_ref": "SPEC-021", "authorized": true, "prev_hash": "efac73aa7ae1f7e0c668a4e4d4bd6efa15264f98dfb44f8f682cb72af5b7e75c", "hash": "1c7e8f326ba480bfd1c5f6be22add1c81c8fb917c899c885e9aaf93f0dbf406d"}
