{"event_id": "evt_20260211_175500_xterm_fix", "ts": "2026-02-11T17:55:00.000000+00:00", "agent": "CLAUDE", "role": "Frontend_Engineer", "action_type": "bug_fix", "description": "Fixed terminal scrolling bug (content sinks off-screen instead of scrolling). Root cause: Tauri CSP (script-src 'self'; style-src 'self') silently blocked xterm.js and xterm.css CDN loads from cdn.jsdelivr.net. Without xterm.css, .xterm-viewport had no position:absolute/top:0/bottom:0 constraints, so it grew infinitely. Fix: downloaded xterm.min.js (283KB), xterm.css (5KB), xterm-addon-fit.min.js (2KB) into adt-console/src/vendor/ and updated index.html to use local paths. CSP now allows them as 'self' resources.", "spec_ref": "SPEC-021", "authorized": true, "prev_hash": "7d230f58796106ac6928c7d16ec450e937db18f0f4f4c71a8d312a75e663dc9c", "hash": "82e648df6e741790274bf33878e595b14000c461bcd6481347a4c5e4aa8cc074"}
{"event_id": "evt_20260211_180000_xterm_postmortem", "ts": "2026-02-11T18:00:00.000000+00:00", "agent": "CLAUDE", "role": "Frontend_Engineer", "action_type": "postmortem", "description": "POSTMORTEM: Terminal scrolling bug (content sinks off-screen). SYMPTOM: Terminal fills correctly top-to-bottom. Once vertical space is full, instead of scrolling, entire content block moves DOWN line-by-line until all text exits through the bottom, leaving black screen. ROOT CAUSE: Tauri CSP in tauri.conf.json (line 32) sets script-src and style-src to 'self' only. xterm.js (v5) and xterm.css were loaded from cdn.jsdelivr.net -- silently blocked by CSP. Without xterm.css, the .xterm-viewport element (which needs position:absolute; top:0; bottom:0 from xterm.css) defaults to position:static with auto height, so it grows infinitely instead of constraining to the .xterm parent. xterm.js internal scrolling depends on .xterm-viewport being height-constrained. WHY SILENT: CSP violations only appear in browser devtools console (not visible in Tauri unless devtools opened). No JS error thrown -- xterm.js was also blocked, so no terminal functionality at all in strict CSP. In some builds it partially worked from browser cache. FIX: Downloaded xterm.min.js, xterm.css, xterm-addon-fit.min.js into adt-console/src/vendor/. Updated index.html to reference vendor/ paths instead of CDN. Files are now embedded in Tauri binary via frontendDist and pass CSP as 'self' resources. PREVENTION: Never use CDN links in Tauri apps. All frontend dependencies must be vendored locally in src/vendor/. Tauri CSP 'self' means only files embedded in the app bundle are allowed.", "spec_ref": "SPEC-021", "authorized": true, "prev_hash": "82e648df6e741790274bf33878e595b14000c461bcd6481347a4c5e4aa8cc074", "hash": "a02e6966b4accc82b34a5c4023bc288723802e6cd756d9ee24a102b4b420ff2e"}
